Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: gruffy
Version: 0.0.1
Summary: Gruffy is Python implemetation of Gruff(Ruby Graphing Library)
Home-page: http://www.hexacosa.net/project/pyprof2html/
Author: Hideo Hattori
Author-email: hhatto.jp@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: About
        =====
        Gruffy is a yet another Pure Python Graphing Library.
        Using `pgmagick`_ (GraphicsMagick) .
        
        .. _`pgmagick`: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pgmagick/
        
        
        Install
        =======
        
            $ pip install gruffy
        
        
        Require
        =======
        `pgmagick`_ module.
        
        package install on Ubuntu::
        
            $ apt-get install libgraphicsmagick++-dev
            $ apt-get install libboost-python1.40-dev
            $ pip install pgmagick
        
        
        Sample Code
        ===========
        
        Bar Graph Sample::
        
            from bar import Bar
        
            g = Bar()
            g.title = "Gruffy's Graph"
        
            g.data("Apples", [1, 2, 3, 4, 4, 3])
            g.data("Oranges", [4, 8, 7, 9, 8, 9])
            g.data("Watermelon", [2, 3, 1, 5, 6, 8])
            g.data("Peaches", [9, 9, 10, 8, 7, 9])
        
            g.labels = {0: '2003', 2: '2004', 4: '2005'}
        
            g.write('sample.png')
        
